<title>BELGIUM: Belgian doctors start strike over hospital plans.</title>
<headline>Belgian doctors start strike over hospital plans.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Belgian hospital doctors, except those covering emergency services, began a four-day strike on Friday to protest against government plans to reorganise the health sector.</p>
<p>The government has put forward financial proposals designed to streamline the nation's hospitals and encourage some of them to merge.</p>
<p>Doctors say the plans threaten not only the jobs of health workers but also the standard of patient care.</p>
<p>The strike, due to last into Monday, is the second in what is likely to be a long running series.</p>
